Digest

public long Digest()
wrap this method if the cell holds any additional state important to the game. This method is called, without a random sequence, to digest the cell in it's usual role. this method can be defined as G.Error("don't call") if you don't use it or don't want to trouble to implement it separately.

drawChip

public boolean drawChip(java.awt.Graphics gc,
                        online.common.exCanvas drawOn,
                        online.game.chip piece,
                        online.common.HitPoint highlight,
                        int SQUARESIZE,
                        int e_x,
                        int e_y,
                        java.lang.String label)
this override demonstrates how to substitute "display only" chips for the canonical chips that are used on the board. In this case, the substutution is to replace generic black and white stones with pretty ones pseudo-randomly assigned to each cell. It's better to do it here because this is where the association between the cell and the stone hasn't been completely forgotten.

Overrides:
drawChip in class online.game.cell<GoCell>
Parameters:
gc - the graphic context to draw on (can be null)
drawOn - the canvas to draw on (corresponding to gc)
piece - the chip to draw
highlight - contains the mouse position, receives info about the hit if any
SQUARESIZE - scale te picture to this size
e_x - x center of the square
e_y - y center of the square
label - after drawing, superimpose this text
Returns:
true if the mouse hit this object.
